        <p>Mr. Townsend establishes the Iowa Primate Learning Sanctuary(IPLS) a nonprofit organization and begins construction of 15 million dollar sanctuary for the purpose of studying language in bonobos and gorillas and humans with language acquisition difficulties. He invites Peter Gabriel and Mr. Woodruff to assist him in moving the bonobos to Iowa. They decline. </p>
        <p>Mr. Townsend visits GSU and gains administrative approval to relocate the bonobos to Iowa for $450,000.00.</p>
        <p>Mr. Townsend promises lifetime care of the bonobos and lifetime positions to Dr. Rumbaugh and Dr. Savage-Rumbaugh in return for GSU agreeing to move the world-renown project to Iowa.</p>
        <p>Peter Gabriel, Steve Woodruff (of the Coca Cola Foundation) and Mr. Hyashibara of the Hyashibara Corporation in  Japan come together to sponsor a plan to move the bonobos to Hawaii in cooperation with the University of Hawaii, Penny Patterson and possibly Roger Fouts to continue the ape language studies.</p>
        <p>Paul McCarntney and his entourage pay a surprise visit to the LRC. Mr. Woodruff is contact by Paul McCartney regarding this visit. He meets Mr. McCartney at the gate and ushers him and his entourage into LRC.  Mr. Woodruff has been a contributor to LRC of significant means and he has strongly opposed the GSU plan to relocate the bonobos to Iowa, on the grounds that the research trajectory will be harmed if this relocation takes place.</p>
        <p>Mr. Townsend arrives at the same time, prepared to make a presentation to the nonprofit entity "ApeNet" which was formed by Mr. Woodruff, Mr. Gabriel and Mr. Hyashibara for the purpose of relocating the bonobo family to a safe location which would allow the research trajectory to flourish and to continue. The presentation of Mr. Townsend is not well received by the members of "ApeNet, " who view Mr. Townsend as interested in establishing a zoological facility for the purpose of making money rather than providing and adequate research facility. </p>
        <p>Mr. Fields supports Mr. Townsend's presentation as does Dr. Washburn. Mr. Fields was a Research Associate that time and responsible for various aspects of the research program, in particular the archiving project and the move toward an anthropological perspective.  Dr. Washburn contacted Mr. Fields to determine how it was that Mr. Cartney and his entourage gained access to the facility. The GSU administration was very upset that the visit had occurred. Mr. Fields explained Mr. Woodruff's role in the event causing a rift between them. Mr. Fields then began working on an operational design for an educational project that would appeal to Mr. Townsend and that would located within the Iowa Child Facility. </p>
        <p>IPLS was officially formed by Mr. Townsend and he begins to relocate funds from tax dollars into the IPLS nonprofit corporation. </p>
        <p>Mr. Townsend determined that he wanted the bonobos to be move to Iowa, so that they might become a part of the Iowa Child Project that he was proposed to build in Iowa.  Mr. Townsend travel to George State University where he met with Georgia State official and provided them with $450,000. In return GSU promised bonobos to Mr. Townsend and a written contract was signed between these two groups (Mr. Townsend and GSU). </p>
