          <p>I am asked to write a grant to NIH and to include the "Orang team" as PI's in the grant and as many Iowans as possible. Researcher's from outside Iowa are looked down upon.   The grant  contains 10 projects and is approximately 600 pages. The Grant is not funded. I am asked to reduce the scope of the projects to three and to reapply. I am informed that I need to demonstrate that data can be collected in Iowa and that I have Institutional support. </p>
          <p>Dr. Beck and Dr. Shoemaker bring complaints against Mr. Brocker, the CEO, and he is removed from his post. He is replaced by Mr. Aipperspach. I do not join in these complaints nor do I deny their validity. </p>
