<p>Panbanisha became clearly pregnant. She ceased mensing and began to exhibit signs of pregnancy.  I explained this to Tyler and indicated that pregnancy tests should be run and that if they were positive she should be place on prenatal vitamins for her health and well-being. However Tyler insisted that that she was not pregnant. He insisted that he ran pregnancy tests and found her not to be pregnant. She produced an still born infant. This infant was most unusual and did not look like any other bonobo baby I had seen previously (I had seen, by that time, two other still born babies - all born in Iowa, and the following live born infants, all born in Atlanta, Kanzi, Panbanisha, Tamuli, Elykia, Maisha, Nyota and Nathan.) This baby was different, very very different. 
